results.name: Number of subsets of {1, 2, ..., n} containing n and having <=3 pairwise coprime elements.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: a(6) = 4 because there are 4 subsets of {1,2,3,4,5,6} containing 6 and having <=3 pairwise coprime elements: {6}, {1,6}, {5,6}, {1,5,6}.
xref: Column 3 of triangle A186975. Sum of A039649 and A185953 for n>1.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Mar 03 2011
